<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1018#">Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1018</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_64.2-1018"/><heading><desig>§ 64.2-1018.</desig><title>Liquidating asset</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> In this section, "liquidating asset" means an asset whose value will diminish or terminate because the asset is expected to produce receipts for a period of limited duration. The term includes a leasehold, patent, copyright, or royalty right, and a right to receive payments during a period of more than one year under an arrangement that does not provide for the payment of interest on the unpaid balance. The term does not include a payment subject to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1017"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1017">§ 64.2-1017<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1017#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, resources subject to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1019"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1019">§ 64.2-1019<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1019#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, timber subject to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1020"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1020">§ 64.2-1020<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1020#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, an activity subject to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1022"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1022">§ 64.2-1022<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1022#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, an asset subject to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1023"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1023">§ 64.2-1023<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1023#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, or any asset for which the trustee establishes a reserve for depreciation under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1026"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1026">§ 64.2-1026<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1026#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A trustee shall allocate to income 10 percent of the receipts from a liquidating asset and the balance to principal.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="1999 VA CH 975"><content><span normalizedCite="1999 Va. Ch. 975">1999, c. 975<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1999#000975#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, § 55-277.19; <citation normalizedCite="2012 VA CH 614"><content><span normalizedCite="2012 Va. Ch. 614">2012, c. 614<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2012#000614#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PW10-004G-K0P1-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 64.2.</desig><title>WILLS, TRUSTS, AND FIDUCIARIES</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="subtitle"><heading><desig>SUBTITLE III.</desig><title>TRUSTS</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 10.</desig><title>UNIFORM PRINCIPAL AND INCOME ACT</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 4.</desig><title>ALLOCATION OF RECEIPTS DURING ADMINISTRATION OF TRUST.</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="part"><heading><desig>PART 3.</desig><title>RECEIPTS NORMALLY APPORTIONED.</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Business &amp; Corporate Compliance</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MUFEMUQ2QTA1OUZCNEE5RjkzNTA2RERFMUNEOTk1RTI7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Royalties</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MTRCNzA4RkUwRjk3NDQ4NTg4N0QzNjkxRTAzNUQwMTQ7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6ODVDRTlENUFGQzU3NDMyNEJEQ0I3QjRENUQ3NDBDRDg</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Estate, Gift &amp; Trust Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OENGNTY0MEQ2RTU